<p>This is simple: Just run the following command:</p>

<p>To delete a Git branch both locally and remotely, first delete the local branch using this command:</p>

<pre><code>git branch -d example
</code></pre>

<p>(Here <code>example</code> is the branch name.)</p>

<p>And after that, delete the remote branch using this command:</p>

<pre><code>git push origin :example
</code></pre>
